+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ThhNNvJMHU8tRiFGTozJ4b","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n     2→\n     3→Add a dead letter queue (DLQ) to capture tasks that have permanently failed after exhausting all retries.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- When a task has no more retries left, it is automatically moved to a dead letter queue associated with its original queue.\n     8→- There should be a way to view all dead-lettered tasks for a given queue.\n     9→- Dead-lettered tasks should retain their error information and a count of how many times they failed.\n    10→- It should be possible to move a dead-lettered task back to its original queue for a fresh round of retries.\n    11→- There should be a way to clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue.\n    12→- Each named queue has its own independent dead letter queue.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5872e38-a990-417f-a2ab-1aa39b657042","uuid":"42fa8852-fa98-4e65-bcdc-7e715575c4ec","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/phases/phase-06.md","content":"# Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n\nAdd a dead letter queue (DLQ) to capture tasks that have permanently failed after exhausting all retries.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- When a task has no more retries left, it is automatically moved to a dead letter queue associated with its original queue.\n- There should be a way to view all dead-lettered tasks for a given queue.\n- Dead-lettered tasks should retain their error information and a count of how many times they failed.\n- It should be possible to move a dead-lettered task back to its original queue for a fresh round of retries.\n- There should be a way to clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue.\n- Each named queue has its own independent dead letter queue.\n","numLines":13,"startLine":1,"totalLines":13}}}
